I am so thankful to my Lord and 
Savior Jesus Christ for giving me the gift of singing. At the age of 53, I still get to use the stage as my playground, sing and dance and goof around. But the bonus is, when people appreciate what I share with them. The tears, laughter and hugs that I receive from them makes me want to do this for as long as my voice and body will allow. I even get to tell them my testimony on how I and my family made it through all our ups and downs all these years, stories to give them hope. God is just so good all the time. I have been consistently working here in the US & Canada since 2021. God has truly done the impossible for me. Oh, and he gives me enough strength in my body so I can drive to the airport, fly, carry my bags, do hair and makeup, iron clothes, order my food and everything else all on my own…mismo! He’s the joy in my heart, the breath in my lungs and the comforter of my soul. 
This photo shows how thankful I am for everything. I’m just sharing this to let you know that God loves us so much that through Him, all things are possible. 

Oh, this was my show in Ottawa, Ontario Canada. Fil Caballes and the whole Gemini Production Team, maraming salamat sa lahat! That’s all. I’m actually in my super long flight na super delayed with wifi para di ma borlot. This 12 hour trip and 1 & 30 mins drive home will knock me out for sure. Can’t wait to see my kiddos and my hubby. 

Up next, show naman with the 3 Divas on June 9…good luck to me!

Praise you Lord for your plans are always good…thank you for making a way for us to move to TEXAS! This is a super late post. It was hard for me to post because I left some memories and amazing friends in Washington state, bittersweet indeed. But now that we have settled and got our things set up, finally feels good to be home. We are staying obedient and surrendered because the Lord has some amazing plans for my family. We’ve seen so countless miracles that I am just in awe. We are so ready for the next chapter. And let me just say, I have the best kids!!! Gavin & Athena, Sabriya & Dylan, I admire you for your patience, help, and determination. You all are truly battled tested. God bless you guys. And to my ❤️ Gary, the best father & leader, thank you for all that you have done. Your direction and strength truly kept us from going nuts. I love you family 🥹 To my brother Isaac, thank you for helping and driving with us. Thank you to our dear friends and family who gave us so much love & did so much for us, we love you, miss you and will always have you in our hearts. Until we see you again, Bremerton & Silverdale WA. ❤️#texans #godisgood #gotidocstrong

Happy New Year to all of you. 

2023 was recovery period for my family. Packed up & left Manila in 2021. Lived in Washington State and survived a devastating fire in 2022. Packed up again and left for Texas. And boy, let me tell y'all...it sure feels so good to finally rest and find peace and respite in Texas. New life, new friends (just a handful), new opportunities and new mercies from our Lord Jesus, who never left or forsaken us. Here is one for all of us, this is pretty powerful. Just give God a try and see His goodness & feel His love and power. Love you and have a blessed 2024 everyone. 

Jeremiah 29:11-14
”For I know the plans I have for you, declares the Lord, plans for welfare and not for evil, to give you a future and a hope. Then you will call upon me and come and pray to me, and I will hear you. You will seek me and find me, when you seek me with all your heart. I will be found by you, declares the Lord, and I will restore your fortunes and gather you from all the nations and all the places where I have driven you, declares the Lord, and I will bring you back to the place from which I sent you into exile.“

P.S. Thank you Glenn & Claire Resilla for having us over for New Year dinner with their fam & friends...
Happy New Year everyone! 🎉🥂❤️
Paalam Paul Chia...may you rest in God's peace 💔
